Job Description:
The ideal candidate should:
Hold at least a Bachelor’s in Computer Science. Master’s in Computer Science/Computer Engineering will be preferred.Have 5 to 10 years of work experience in the relevant field Job Description Responsible for the complete end-to-end process of Database design & operations, including implementation, maintenance activities and configuration reviews.Responsible for all activities relating to CRM DB productions, including new implementations and migrationsMaintain development and testing databases to ensure integrity, performance, accessibility, and recoverability of data.Develop long-term strategy for historical data retention and archival plan for storage needs; assess data retention, backup, and recovery.Coordinate with concerned teams to ensure any new implementations, changes and migrations that might impact the controlled DBs, are fully understood. (e.g. concerned team’s application, network and infrastructure across Mobilink).Manage a team to achieve business objectives including the attainment of targets for operations support customer satisfaction, employee satisfaction, service levels, resolution time, and project deadlines.Represent the CRM systems team on cross-organizational teams to deliver on organizational objectives.Manage workflows and schedules for direct reports and ensure adequate workload coverage.Participate in CRM change management process to ensure best practices.Act as product expert to align internal clients’ goals with newly released / enhanced CRM features.Partner with internal clients and CRM team members to define, document & fix operational system bugs/ issues.Responsible for requirements definition/translation to technical specifications, workflow customization, report development and training documentation to support CRM Adoption, best practice, data management and reporting.Play an instrumental role in the Definition, documentation, and implementation of CRM-related policies and procedures.Plan, review and customize the CRM application as prioritized to meet needs of CRM internal clients / consumers of data coordination / leadership of QA and UAT for prioritized initiative.Assist with on-call support/ coordination when applicable (24/7 operations management).Manage databases, including security, space management, database migrations, database and system tuning, database refreshes, backups and restores, and user resource management.Maintain development and testing databases to ensure integrity, performance, accessibility, and recoverability of data.Develop long-term strategy for historical data retention and archival plan for storage needs; define data retention, backup, and recovery for all data.Recommend and implement new Oracle features or software enhancements.Troubleshoot and tune for system and performance problems; identify and resolve information flow, content issues, and assist with transformation of business requirements into logical data models.Work in an operations environment with project managers in application department and direct multiple projects like coordinating Oracle Support and ACS, from the development environment to pre-production environment through the build process and ultimately migration to production.Work with other infrastructure personnel to design proper hardware infrastructure.Update DB with latest CPU and PSU patches for proactive maintenance.Manage and support all PROD and DEV instances of Oracle 10g and above.Create and manage primary database storage structures like table spaces, data files etc.
Essential Skills Oracle Database Certified (10G/11G)Excellent written and verbal skillsAbility to communicate with users of Oracle databasesOS expertise in Solaris, HP UX,Linux and WindowsAbility to work in teams Desirable Skills Oracle RAC,Oracle LDAP & Siebel (Oracle CRM)Oracle Exadata and Exalogic.Proficiency in MS Office Suite, Visio, Database and monitoring tools etcStrong communication and leadership skillsAbility to do issue analysis and work under high pressureAbility to manage 24x7 operations
